    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The Whole Point of the Deck is to make sure things die or get currupted.<br />
<br />
Eowyn wounds the heck outta things with her skirmish ability.  However, since many Uruks negate her ability, Legolas, Arwen, and Faramir&#39;s Bow are added for good measure.  Quick as may be is devastating, although, some might substitute it for Baruk Khazad.  Faramir is there for the awesome &quot;doom drove them&quot; and For Help in Doubt and Need.<br />
<br />
<br />
The Shadow side is simple:  It is likely you will get The Witch King within the first few turns of the game, which is amazing, as it can shine early in the game, when more companions tend to get played.  Try and work it so Ulaire Cantea makes his appearence at Slag Mounds. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
